meanings.english_definition: A female given name, a diminutive of Victoria or a variant of Tori.

meanings.definition: (historical) A member of the Tory party in Scotland.
meanings.english_definition: (historical) A member of the Tory party in Scotland, particularly during the late 17th and early 18th centuries.

etymology.value: As a surname, likely of Scottish origin. As a given name, a diminutive of Victoria or a variant of Tori.
